{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778227054,"nonce":"J5xSY+JItUa8o8UQJFERRn24rYA=","message":"**Induced-gain analyser run on flavor-(b) controllers — pre-registered metric resolved (this batch).** Companion to the flagged follow-up in coord comment `48d9368` of 2026-05-08. Branch `feature/induced-gain-flavor-b`. Substantive details and tables on `74bfd86`.\n\n**Headline `γ_sd × qr_cost`**: flavor-B median = **154.78** (45 replicates, 9 configs); flavor-A baselines median = **163.39** (first-run, excl. degenerate); ratio = **0.947** (≈ 5% reduction). η_max trend in γ_sd is **flat** (152.5 → 156.2 → 154.8), NOT a U-shape; this also disambiguates the U-shape in `c723082` training ctrl_loss as most likely a saddle-dynamics reporting artifact rather than a robustness inversion.\n\n**Cross-cutting consequences for analyses**:\n\n1. **`γ_sd × qr_cost` does NOT discriminate flavor (a) ⊊ (b) on this single canonical reach.** The pre-registered headline channel is empirically uninformative for cross-flavor discrimination. This re-frames the next analysis pass: the operator-norm-on-one-linearisation metric is direction-insensitive and may miss training-relevant ΔA directions.\n2. **`γ_sp × qr_cost` continues to discriminate cross-method**, including for flavor-B (median 0.95-1.39, comparable to or below the best flavor-A minimax at 1.32-2.14). Reinforces the first-run finding (this coord comment `4dd33b8`) that γ_sp is the empirical headline for cross-method discrimination, NOT γ_af or γ_sd.\n3. **The (a) ⊊ (b) test is not yet conclusively run.** A direction-projected variant of the induced-gain analyser (project onto trained-against ΔA directions rather than worst-case) would be the natural next step. Tier-guess: desirable, on the methodology-fix critical path. No new analyser issue filed yet — will file if the direction-projected version is committed to in conversation.\n4. **Methodological hygiene worked**: 5 replicates per group with the 10× rule produced zero false-positive flags on the headline channel; auxiliary channels caught 5+8 single-replicate outliers (parallels the first-run mult_single rep-0 pattern and reinforces the `4fd0388` hygiene principle).\n\nCross-ref: comment on `74bfd86` for the full report; `c723082` for the input training; `48d9368` for the follow-up flag this resolves.","files":null}]}